ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Windows Kernel IGMPv3 and MLDv2 Request Processing Code Execution (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: There exists a remote code execution vulnerability in the Microsoft Windows TCP/IP stack driver. The flaw is due to insufficient validation when processing Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) messages and Multicast Listener Discovery (MLD) messages. An unauthenticated remote attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code with elevated privileges or create a system wide denial of service condition on the target host. (IPv6 Version)
